directions: Mix onion, garlic, chicken broth, cumin, oregano, salt and Tabasco in 3 1/2 to 6-quart crockpot. Add chicken. Stir in beans, corn, and cilantro, if using. Cover and cook on LOW for 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 hours, or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken; chop or shred chicken. Return chicken to crockpot. Cover and cook on low 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

Per Serving (excluding unknown items): 209 Calories; 2g Fat (7.9% calories from fat); 26g Protein; 21g Carbohydrate; 5g Dietary Fiber; 46mg Cholesterol; 337mg Sodium. Exchanges: 1 1/2 Grain(Starch); 3 Lean Meat; 0 Vegetable; 0 Fat.
ingredients: 4 15-oz cans great northern beans, canned; drained, rinsed
title: White Chicken Chili
